    "created_at": "2017-06-19T08:32:19Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-19T08:32:47Z",
    "body": "This also occurs on older hardware, not just inside virtual machines. I just received a very similar bug report from MacBook Pro 2012 user and `--disable-gpu` flag solved the problem for him.\r\n\r\nI think Chrome has a blacklist of untested/unsupported/legacy GPUs which is used to determine whether hardware acceleration should be enabled by default. Perhaps Electron could use the same approach?"
  },
